From: Wim Taymans <wtaymans@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2015 11:46:36 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] man: improve manpage

Mention the PULSE_COOKIE environment variable.
---
 man/pulseaudio.1.xml.in | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/man/pulseaudio.1.xml.in b/man/pulseaudio.1.xml.in
index 8810e90..b44e1cf 100644
--- a/man/pulseaudio.1.xml.in
+++ b/man/pulseaudio.1.xml.in
@@ -440,6 +440,10 @@ USA.
 
     <p><arg>$PULSE_CLIENTCONFIG</arg>: path of file that shall be read instead of <file>client.conf</file> (see above) for client configuration.</p>
 
+    <p><arg>$PULSE_COOKIE</arg>: path of file that contains the PulseAudio
+    authentication cookie. Defaults to <file>~/.pulse-cookie</file>.
+    The cookie must be shared between users that want to connect to the same server.</p>
+
     <p>These environment settings take precedence -- if set -- over the configuration settings from <file>client.conf</file> (see above).</p>
 
   </section>
